The paper deals with content-based image retrieval (CBIR), which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The authors also mention the use of matrix operations, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
